#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:3
msgid "Contribution getting started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:5
msgid ""
"Contributions are highly welcomed and appreciated.  Every little help "
"counts, so do not hesitate!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:10
msgid "Contribution links"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:15
msgid "Feature requests and feedback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:17
msgid "Do you like pytest?  Share some love on Twitter or in your blog posts!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:19
msgid ""
"We'd also like to hear about your propositions and suggestions.  Feel free "
"to `submit them as issues <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues>`_ "
"and:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:22
msgid "Explain in detail how they should work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:23
msgid ""
"Keep the scope as narrow as possible.  This will make it easier to implement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:29
msgid "Report bugs"
msgstr "回報臭蟲"

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:31
msgid ""
"Report bugs for pytest in the `issue tracker <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:33
msgid "If you are reporting a bug, please include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:35
msgid "Your operating system name and version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:36
msgid ""
"Any details about your local setup that might be helpful in troubleshooting, "
"specifically Python interpreter version, installed libraries and pytest "
"version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:39
msgid "Detailed steps to reproduce the bug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:41
msgid ""
"If you can write a demonstration test that currently fails but should pass "
"(xfail), that is a very useful commit to make as well, even if you can't "
"find how to fix the bug yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:49
msgid "Fix bugs"
msgstr "修復臭蟲"

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:51
msgid ""
"Look through the GitHub issues for bugs.  Here is sample filter you can use: "
"https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/labels/bug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:54
msgid ""
":ref:`Talk <contact>` to developers to find out how you can fix specific "
"bugs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:56
msgid ""
"Don't forget to check the issue trackers of your favourite plugins, too!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:61
msgid "Implement features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:63
msgid ""
"Look through the GitHub issues for enhancements.  Here is sample filter you "
"can use: https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/labels/enhancement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:67
msgid ""
":ref:`Talk <contact>` to developers to find out how you can implement "
"specific features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:71
msgid "Write documentation"
msgstr "撰寫文件"

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:73
msgid "pytest could always use more documentation.  What exactly is needed?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:75
msgid ""
"More complementary documentation.  Have you perhaps found something unclear?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:76
msgid "Documentation translations.  We currently have only English."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:77
msgid "Docstrings.  There can never be too many of them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:78
msgid "Blog posts, articles and such -- they're all very appreciated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:80
msgid ""
"You can also edit documentation files directly in the Github web interface "
"without needing to make a fork and local copy. This can be convenient for "
"small fixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:88
msgid "Submitting Plugins to pytest-dev"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:90
msgid ""
"Pytest development of the core, some plugins and support code happens in "
"repositories living under the ``pytest-dev`` organisations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:93
msgid "`pytest-dev on GitHub <https://github.com/pytest-dev>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:95
msgid "`pytest-dev on Bitbucket <https://bitbucket.org/pytest-dev>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:97
msgid ""
"All pytest-dev Contributors team members have write access to all contained "
"repositories.  pytest core and plugins are generally developed using `pull "
"requests`_ to respective repositories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:101
msgid "The objectives of the ``pytest-dev`` organisation are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:103
msgid "Having a central location for popular pytest plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:104
msgid ""
"Sharing some of the maintenance responsibility (in case a maintainer no "
"longer whishes to maintain a plugin)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:106
msgid ""
"You can submit your plugin by subscribing to the `pytest-dev mail list "
"<https://mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/pytest-dev>`_ and writing a mail "
"pointing to your existing pytest plugin repository which must have the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:111
msgid ""
"PyPI presence with a ``setup.py`` that contains a license, ``pytest-`` "
"prefixed name, version number, authors, short and long description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:114
msgid "a ``tox.ini`` for running tests using `tox <http://tox.testrun.org>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:116
msgid ""
"a ``README.txt`` describing how to use the plugin and on which platforms it "
"runs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:119
msgid ""
"a ``LICENSE.txt`` file or equivalent containing the licensing information, "
"with matching info in ``setup.py``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:122
msgid "an issue tracker for bug reports and enhancement requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:124
msgid ""
"If no contributor strongly objects and two agree, the repository can then be "
"transferred to the ``pytest-dev`` organisation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:127
msgid ""
"Here's a rundown of how a repository transfer usually proceeds (using a "
"repository named ``joedoe/pytest-xyz`` as example):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:130
msgid "One of the ``pytest-dev`` administrators creates:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:132
msgid ""
"``pytest-xyz-admin`` team, with full administration rights to ``pytest-dev/"
"pytest-xyz``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:134
msgid ""
"``pytest-xyz-developers`` team, with write access to ``pytest-dev/pytest-"
"xyz``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:137
msgid "``joedoe`` is invited to the ``pytest-xyz-admin`` team;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:139
msgid ""
"After accepting the invitation, ``joedoe`` transfers the repository from its "
"original location to ``pytest-dev/pytest-xyz`` (A nice feature is that "
"GitHub handles URL redirection from the old to the new location "
"automatically)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:143
msgid ""
"``joedoe`` is free to add any other collaborators to the ``pytest-xyz-"
"admin`` or ``pytest-xyz-developers`` team as desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:146
msgid ""
"The ``pytest-dev/Contributors`` team has write access to all projects, and "
"every project administrator is in it. We recommend that each plugin has at "
"least three people who have the right to release to PyPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:150
msgid ""
"Repository owners can be assured that no ``pytest-dev`` administrator will "
"ever make releases of your repository or take ownership in any way, except "
"in rare cases where someone becomes unresponsive after months of contact "
"attempts. As stated, the objective is to share maintenance and avoid "
"\"plugin-abandon\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:160
msgid "Preparing Pull Requests on GitHub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:162
msgid ""
"There's an excellent tutorial on how Pull Requests work in the `GitHub Help "
"Center <https://help.github.com/articles/using-pull-requests/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:167
msgid ""
"What is a \"pull request\"?  It informs project's core developers about the "
"changes you want to review and merge.  Pull requests are stored on `GitHub "
"servers <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/pulls>`_. Once you send pull "
"request, we can discuss it's potential modifications and even add more "
"commits to it later on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:173
msgid ""
"There's an excellent tutorial on how Pull Requests work in the `GitHub Help "
"Center <https://help.github.com/articles/using-pull-requests/>`_, but here "
"is a simple overview:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:177
msgid ""
"Fork the `pytest GitHub repository <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest>`__.  It's fine to use ``pytest`` as your fork repository name "
"because it will live under your user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:182
msgid ""
"Clone your fork locally using `git <https://git-scm.com/>`_ and create a "
"branch::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:184
msgid ""
"$ git clone git@github.com:YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/pytest.git\n"
"$ cd pytest\n"
"# now, to fix a bug create your own branch off \"master\":\n"
"\n"
"    $ git checkout -b your-bugfix-branch-name master\n"
"\n"
"# or to instead add a feature create your own branch off \"features\":\n"
"\n"
"    $ git checkout -b your-feature-branch-name features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:194
msgid ""
"Given we have \"major.minor.micro\" version numbers, bugfixes will usually "
"be released in micro releases whereas features will be released in minor "
"releases and incompatible changes in major releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:198
msgid ""
"If you need some help with Git, follow this quick start guide: https://git."
"wiki.kernel.org/index.php/QuickStart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:201
msgid "Install tox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:203
msgid ""
"Tox is used to run all the tests and will automatically setup virtualenvs to "
"run the tests in. (will implicitly use http://www.virtualenv.org/en/"
"latest/)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:207
msgid "$ pip install tox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:209
msgid "Run all the tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:211
msgid ""
"You need to have Python 2.7 and 3.5 available in your system.  Now running "
"tests is as simple as issuing this command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:214
msgid "$ python runtox.py -e linting,py27,py35"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:216
msgid ""
"This command will run tests via the \"tox\" tool against Python 2.7 and 3.5 "
"and also perform \"lint\" coding-style checks.  ``runtox.py`` is a thin "
"wrapper around ``tox`` which installs from a development package index where "
"newer (not yet released to pypi) versions of dependencies (especially "
"``py``) might be present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:222
msgid "You can now edit your local working copy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:224
msgid ""
"You can now make the changes you want and run the tests again as necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:226
msgid ""
"To run tests on py27 and pass options to pytest (e.g. enter pdb on failure) "
"to pytest you can do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:229
msgid "$ python runtox.py -e py27 -- --pdb"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:231
msgid "or to only run tests in a particular test module on py35::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:233
msgid "$ python runtox.py -e py35 -- testing/test_config.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:235
msgid ""
"Commit and push once your tests pass and you are happy with your change(s)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:237
msgid ""
"$ git commit -a -m \"<commit message>\"\n"
"$ git push -u"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:240
msgid ""
"Make sure you add a CHANGELOG message, and add yourself to AUTHORS. If you "
"are unsure about either of these steps, submit your pull request and we'll "
"help you fix it up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:244
msgid ""
"Finally, submit a pull request through the GitHub website using this data::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:246
msgid ""
"head-fork: YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/pytest\n"
"compare: your-branch-name\n"
"\n"
"base-fork: pytest-dev/pytest\n"
"base: master          # if it's a bugfix\n"
"base: feature         # if it's a feature"
msgstr ""
